		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Uncharted Waters have 16kB SRAM while Just Breed uses only 8kB, but it will still work fine with 16kB. To have extra sound, you'd just have to add resistors and capacitors on the free slots on the PCB and then mix the sound inside the NES by modifing it somehow (I also did this, but with pin 18 instead of pin 54 wich is "officially" used by NES board).
<br />Without buying the japanese Just Breed cart, I could never have figured this stuff out.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
